comments.body:
@cabo comment:

Just making that change makes large ranges look the same, even if parts of them have much stronger review requirements (and, unfortunately, processing times) than others.

We should have a pair of terms like “expert quick review” and “deep expert review” to distinguish these with high visibility to the registrants.

Splitting the range might be trickier than one might imagine:
1. At this time, defining a boundary would be arbitrary guesswork;
2. There are pre-existing allocations that are adjacent and fall in different policies (e.g., 10003 is Expert Review, 10002 is FCFS).

@thomas-fossati New commit added. This should be checked with IANA also.

I belief that any procedure for "entry removal" for temporary entries should be in 4.2.
Only procedures for updating the "Media Type" hyperlink field should be in 4.3. Therefore, I've removed the removal process from 4.3 and included it in 4.2.
